# gen196 — Python by DELTA (CODE-MASTERY.md §7b, language-as-delta). A Python
# front-end (code_ingest_py) emits the SAME abstract facts as C — code_function/1
# and code_calls/2, scoped by indentation instead of braces — so EVERY downstream
# analyzer (defines / call-graph / cross-file locate) works on Python unchanged.
# The reasoning is shared; only the surface syntax is derived. Fixture:
# tests/code/py/sample.py.
#expect: pass
#faculty: python-by-delta
# F2 — function definitions, from `def name(...):`.
> which functions are defined in tests/code/py/sample.py
< it defines pyadd, pysquare and pymain
# F3 — the call graph, attributed by indentation scope.
> what does pymain call in tests/code/py/sample.py
< pymain calls pyadd and pysquare
# F4 (by-name) — cross-file localization now spans .py too (same code_locate).
> which file under tests/code/py defines pysquare
< pysquare is defined in sample.py
# Bilingual: Italian cues reach the SAME path (funzioni/definite, chiama).
> quali funzioni sono definite in tests/code/py/sample.py
< it defines pyadd, pysquare and pymain
> cosa chiama pymain in tests/code/py/sample.py
< pymain calls pyadd and pysquare
